			<h2>A little disapointed</h2>
			<p>After buying a new grill every 2 (or less) years and getting upset that my grill kept falling apart, I finally took my best friend's recommendation and bought a Weber Genesis Gas Grill. I balked at the price, but when you consider that you buy a Brinkmann (or other) grill for $400 every 2 years, I think this one will pay for itself. I grill about 3 times a week - and when I grilled the first time I could tell right away I made the right choice in getting a Weber. Solid construction, good heat distribution, and quality materials make this grill worth the money. I am still figuring out how to grill on this one, and I have obviously gone to the major leagues - there is a huge difference between this one and the grills I used to buy. I am now a fan, and realize I was missing the boat all this time.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

