				<div class="star-off"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
			</div>
			<h2>Never buy this!</h2>
			<p>I have had many grills over the years. Most in the $300-$500 range and most will last 4-5 years. Spring through Fall we grill 4-5 nights a week. It was time to replace, and while we were looking and researching my wife opened the lid on a Weber 330. When she did she said, " this is the one, I can feel the difference in the weight of the lid". I had stayed away from Weber before because I didn't believe it was worth the difference in price. I can now say after having my Weber 330 for a while, it is the best grill I've ever had. I love the fact that I have such control over the temperature. I can control It from 200 to 650 with ease. With the burner warranty 10 years, I plan on having this grill for a long time. There were many other grills we looked at with equal or lesser cost, that had comparable and even more features. In my humble opinion, The Weber 330 has all you need and better quality and durability. I love my Weber 330, and am thankful my wife pushed this tight wad to spend the extra for quality.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="4-star cf">
		<div class="review-author">
			<h4>By GrillLover</h4>
			From Columbia MO<br />
