		</div>
		<div class="review-content">
			<div class="score-small">
				<div class="star-on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
				<div class="star-on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
				<div class="star-on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
				<div class="star-on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
				<div class="star-off"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
			</div>
			<h2>I love this thing</h2>
			<p>Instructions pretty straight forward. Use a socket wrench instead of the bad little wrench enclosed in the box... throw that one away. It took me about 3 hours by myself but would take less if you had a helper. You find out what a great piece if machinery (art) this is by putting it together. Very solid construction. Being fairly experienced at grilling I did not think this grill would cook any better.... I was wrong. Really cooks better. Much better range of heat... lots higher heat to a very even low setting. Just LOVE the sear section.... works great. Very controllable heat really makes a difference. Because it has such great construction and very easily replacement of parts I am looking forward to many years of happy grilling... thanks to Weber!</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="1-star cf">
		<div class="review-author">
			<h4>By Beth H</h4>
			From Wildwood, NJ<br />
			Pro Griller
		</div>
		<div class="review-content">
			<div class="score-small">
				<div class="star-on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
